OWASP ESAPI for ColdFusion/CFML Project
* This project is still in development *
Purpose: This is the ColdFusion/CFML language version of OWASP ESAPI.
License: BSD license

* NOTE: As of August 2011 this is now the official CFESAPI project *


*** SETUP/USAGE - MORE INFO TO COME ***

Setup:
1. The cfesapi folder should sit at the webroot level.
2. Copy /cfesapi/esapi/esapi-2.0_rc10.jar and selected files from /cfesapi/esapi/libs/ to your lib folder (see compatibility below).
4. Restart ColdFusion.

Tests:
- You can run the MXUnit tests using: /cfesapi/test/index.cfm

Demo:
- See the /cfesapi/demo/ for examples of implementation.

Implementation:
- You can extend any of the default implementations to overwrite the methods you need
 and/or
- You can create new implementations that implement the provided interfaces

How:
- Copy the /cfesapi/esapi/configuration/.esapi/ folder to another location and make changes to your copy
- In your code, call ESAPI.securityConfiguration().setResourceDirectory("your config path")
- Be sure to update the ESAPI.properties file with the location of your implementation CFC
- Include the /cfesapi/helpers/ESAPI.cfm in your application.


*** COMPATIBILITY ***

**************************
* Adobe ColdFusion 9.0.1 *
**************************
MXUnit Test Results
 - 252 total = 3 failures + 4 errors + 245 successes

Dependencies (place in [webroot]\WEB-INF\cfusion\lib)
- ESAPI.jar (not needed if you have HF: http://kb2.adobe.com/cps/907/cpsid_90784.html)
- antisamy.jar
- batik-css.jar
- batik-util.jar
- commons-configuration.jar

**************************
* Railo ColdFusion 3.2.3 *
**************************
MXUnit Test Results
- 252 total = 1 failures + 10 errors + 241 successes

Dependencies (place in [webroot]\WEB-INF\railo\lib)
- ESAPI.jar
- antisamy.jar
- batik-css.jar
- batik-util.jar
- commons-beanutils.jar
- commons-configuration.jar
- nekohtml.jar
- xercesImpl.jar
